<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06036062 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06036062 </ACCESS><CAPTION>  Photo; PHOTO: Associated Press; CHARGE IT -- Sacramento's Lionel Simmons drawsa foul from Scottie Pippen (33) during a 108-97 loss to the Bulls.  </CAPTION><DESCRIPT>  PROFESSIONAL; BASKETBALL; CLUB; GAME; BRIEF  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  Coming off the bench to lead his team to victory is nothing new for swingmanEddie Johnson.;    It's something the Seattle SuperSonics hoped he would dowhen they acquired him from Phoenix in December.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Sports  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  JOHNSON SCORES 34 AS SEATTLE WINSHORNETS CAN'T STOP SIXTH MAN  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  BasketballNBA Roundup  </MEMO><TEXT>     In Charlotte, N.C., on Monday, Johnson played his sixth-man role toperfection -- getting 34 points and six rebounds to lead the Sonics to a100-93 victory over the Charlotte Hornets.;    Johnson had help. Michael Cagefinished with 18 rebounds, and Shawn Kemp had 17 points and 13 rebounds.;   &quot;It felt really good tonight,&quot; said Johnson, a well-traveled 10-year veteran.&quot;It has for the last month. My shot has really been there. Tonight we neededsomeone to get hot.;    &quot;I hit my first few shots and the guys started lookingfor me.&quot;;    Down the stretch for Seattle, however, defense was the key.;   The Sonics held the Hornets scoreless for two minutes late in the fourthquarter and outrebounded them 19-6 in the period.;    With Charlotte leading90-87 and 2 minutes, 9 seconds remaining, Seattle's Olden Polynice reboundedJohnson's miss and dunked. Charlotte's J.R. Reid then turned the ball over toJohnson, who was fouled and hit two free throws to give Seattle the lead forgood with 1:30 left.;    &quot;It's one of those games that you let get away,&quot;Charlotte Coach Gene Littles said. &quot;We had a chance to win it. We missed a tonof free throws.;    Seattle made 28 of 35 foul shots to Charlotte's 14 of 25.; TRAIL BLAZERS 117, NETS 102: Portland's reserves scored 53 points, led byCliff Robinson's 20, as the Trail Blazers improved their NBA-best record withthe rout of New Jersey in Portland, Ore.;    The Blazers are 39-8 overall and24-2 at home. The Nets have lost five straight, all on the road.;  BULLS 108,KINGS 97: Chicago won just its second road game in the past seven outings,defeating Sacramento to pull within one game of first-place Detroit in theCentral Division.;  BUCKS 103, CAVALIERS 96: In Richfield, Ohio, Ricky Piercescored 20 points in the second half and Jeff Grayer had 11 in the fourthquarter as Milwaukee beat Cleveland to end its nine-game road losing streak.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Mercury News Wire Services  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  SAN JOSE MERCURY NEWS  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910205  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Tuesday  </DAY><MONTH>  February  </MONTH><PG.COL>  4C  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><FEATURE>  PHOTO  </FEATURE><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  397  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Tuesday February 5, 199100036062,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>